headline: PayPal's Venmo, Snowflake upgrade, Asana: Trending Tickers
summary: PayPal-owned (PYPL) mobile payment app Venmo is adding new features to its platform, including 15% cashback rewards at select retailers. UBS analysts upgrade Snowflake stock (SNOW) to a Buy rating and raise their price target to $265 per share. Asana (ASAN) shares sink Wednesday morning after topping first quarter earnings estimates while reporting a notable year-over-year decline in sales growth. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Wealth here.

headline: Venmo Unleashes Next Phase of Commerce with the Venmo Debit Card and Venmo Checkout
summary: Venmo, a leading social payments platform, today announced an accelerated expansion of its commerce capabilities, introducing even more benefits for customers to use their Venmo balance beyond peer-to-peer payments - from everyday purchases to earning enhanced rewards in-store and online with the Venmo Debit Mastercard®1.

headline: Mizuho updates U.S. top picks: Adds CVS Health, PayPal and Oracle
summary: Investing.com -- Mizuho has updated its U.S. Top Picks list for June, adding CVS Health (NYSE:CVS), PayPal (NASDAQ:PYPL) and Oracle (NYSE:ORCL) to its highest-conviction ideas, alongside ConocoPhillips (NYSE:COP), First Solar (NASDAQ:FSLR), Insmed (NASDAQ:INSM), Corteva (NYSE:CTVA), and Carrier Global (NYSE:CARR).
